      "role": "user",
      "content": "I'm looking at some digitized records for the 1780 census in a particular county in Virginia. I've noticed a really strange dip in the recorded population between the 1770s and 1790s that doesn't seem to align with the known mortality rates from the Revolutionary War or typical migration patterns for that region. What are some of the standard historical explanations for such sudden, unexplained population fluctuations in late 18th-century colonial records?",
